### **14. PCODE INSTRUCTION DECODING**

**File:** `src/debugger.rs`, lines 313-352

```rust
fn decode_pcode_at(&self, code_base: u32, offset: u32) -> PcodeInstr {
    let addr = code_base + offset;
    let opcode = self.emulator.read_byte(addr);
    let (name, operand, size) = Self::decode_pcode_opcode(opcode, addr, &self.emulator);
    PcodeInstr { addr: offset, name, operand, size }
}

fn decode_pcode_opcode(opcode: u8, addr: u32, emu: &EmulatorCore) 
    -> (&'static str, Option<u32>, u32) 
{
    match opcode {
        // 3-byte operand (push, jmp, call, etc.)
        0x01 | 0x30 | 0x31 | 0x32 | 0x33 | 0x35 => {
            let operand = emu.read_word(addr + 1) & 0xFFFFFF;
            (name, Some(operand), 4)
        }
        // 1-byte operand (push_s, trap, enter, etc.)
        0x02 | 0x36 | 0x40..=0x4B | 0x60 => {
            let operand = emu.read_byte(addr + 1) as u32;
            (name, Some(operand), 2)
        }
        // No operand
        _ => (name, None, 1)
    }
}
```

**P-Code Opcodes (lines 25-75):**
```
0x00  halt      0x33  call       0x45  storeg
0x01  push      0x34  ret        0x46  addrl
0x02  push_s    0x35  calln      0x47  addrg
0x03  dup       0x36  trap       0x48  loada
0x04  drop      0x40  enter      0x49  storea
0x05  swap      0x41  leave      0x4A  loadn
0x06  over      0x42  loadl      0x4B  storen
0x10  add       0x43  storel     0x50  load
0x11  sub       0x44  loadg      0x51  store
...etc...
```

---

## SUMMARY

The web-dv24r execution model is a **two-level system**:

1. **COR24 Host Level** — pvm.s (COR24 assembly) implements a fetch-decode-execute VM
2. **P-Code VM Level** — Runs p-code on the COR24 virtual machine

**Key Design Principles:**
- **Pre-assembled binaries** — pvm.s and demos assembled at build time, not runtime
- **Batch execution** — 50K instructions per 25ms tick prevents browser blocking
- **Data relocation** — Loader scans `push` instructions and rewrites data references to absolute addresses
- **No binary linker** — All linking happens at `.spc` text level (pl24r), then assembly to `.p24`
- **Position-independent code** — P-code addresses are segment-relative; loader places segments and sets base registers

This architecture enables **interactive debugging in the browser** with two-level stepping (p-code and host COR24), UART I/O, and real-time instruction execution at ~2M instructions/second.

